result.execSummary:
The defendant David N Zuhlke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Shall pay fine + costs within 60 days or set payment plan with Clerk of Courts.

Defendant, David N Zuhlke in court, Gilbert Grant Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Also present is def's father, Douglas Zuhlke.  Court questions def on waiver of attorney;  court accepts waiver.  Court reviews chgs and pens.  Guilty plea entered;  court accepts plea and finds def guilty.  State heard on sentencing recomendations.  Court heard and imposes sentence as follows:

$100 fine + costs

9:20 - Defendant, David N Zuhlke in court, Gilbert Grant Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant has received copy of Criminal Complaint and advised of rights, charges and penalties. Court finds probable cause. P&S set. Court sets $500 PA bond with conditions:   Defendant shall have his/her fingerprints and photographs taken at the Dodge County Sheriff's Department, Jail Division.  Defendant shall not use/possess/control any controlled substances (without a valid prescription therefore) or drug paraphernalia, nor be in the presence of anyone who does.
